aiSLCDiscrete.description: MIB module for SLCs with discrete input and output points.

aiSLCDiscreteInputTable.name: aiSLCDiscreteInputTable
aiSLCDiscreteInputTable.description: Table of discrete input points indexed by point number. Includes description, configuration, and status information.

aislcdinPointNumber.name: aislcdinPointNumber
aislcdinPointNumber.description: Input point number to which this table row applies.

aislcdinDescription.name: aislcdinDescription
aislcdinDescription.description: Textual description of the point. Maximum length is 80 characters.

aislcdinNormalInput.name: aislcdinNormalInput
aislcdinNormalInput.description: Input that corresponds to the point's normal state.

aislcdinAlarmSeverity.name: aislcdinAlarmSeverity
aislcdinAlarmSeverity.description: Severity of the point's alarm state, or notReported(5) if the point does not generate an alarm.

aislcdinNormalStateText.name: aislcdinNormalStateText
aislcdinNormalStateText.description: Textual description of the point's normal state. Maximum length is 80 characters.

aislcdinAlarmStateText.name: aislcdinAlarmStateText
aislcdinAlarmStateText.description: Textual description of the point's alarm state. Maximum length is 80 characters.

aislcdinCurrentInput.name: aislcdinCurrentInput
aislcdinCurrentInput.description: The current input to the point.

aislcdinLastChangeTime.name: aislcdinLastChangeTime
aislcdinLastChangeTime.description: Textual representation of the time of the most recent input change. 24-hour format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS.

aislcdinCurrentState.name: aislcdinCurrentState
aislcdinCurrentState.description: The point's current alarm state, or normal(5).

aislcdinCurrentStateText.name: aislcdinCurrentStateText
aislcdinCurrentStateText.description: Textual description of the point's current state. This is either aislcdinNormalStateText or aislcdinAlarmStateText.

aislcdintl1AccessID.name: aislcdintl1AccessID
aislcdintl1AccessID.description: Unique TL1 access identifier for this point. Maximum length is 22 characters.

aislcdintl1Provisioned.name: aislcdintl1Provisioned
aislcdintl1Provisioned.description: Enable TL1 management of this point.

aislcdintl1AccessIDType.name: aislcdintl1AccessIDType
aislcdintl1AccessIDType.description: Identifies the point as either an equipment(1) alarm condition or an environmental(2) alarm.

aislcdintl1NotificationCode.name: aislcdintl1NotificationCode
aislcdintl1NotificationCode.description: Severity of the point's alarm state.

aislcdintl1ServiceAffecting.name: aislcdintl1ServiceAffecting
aislcdintl1ServiceAffecting.description: Indicates whether or not the alarm affects the functioning of the equipment. This is only meaningful when aislcdintl1AccessIDType is equipment(1).

aislcdintl1ConditionType.name: aislcdintl1ConditionType
aislcdintl1ConditionType.description: String indicating the type of alarm condition, used only when aislcdintl1AccessIDType is equipment(1). Maximum length is 20 characters.

aislcdintl1ConditionDescription.name: aislcdintl1ConditionDescription
aislcdintl1ConditionDescription.description: Textual description of the alarm condition, used only when aislcdintl1AccessIDType is equipment(1). Maximum length is 64 characters.

aislcdintl1AlarmType.name: aislcdintl1AlarmType
aislcdintl1AlarmType.description: String indicating the type of alarm, used only when aislcdintl1AccessIDType is environmental(2). Maximum length is 10 characters.

aislcdintl1AlarmMessage.name: aislcdintl1AlarmMessage
aislcdintl1AlarmMessage.description: Textual description of the alarm, used only when aislcdintl1AccessIDType is environmental(2). Maximum length is 40 characters.

aislcdinDebounceValue.name: aislcdinDebounceValue
aislcdinDebounceValue.description: Number of 100 msec intervals to wait for the input to stop bouncing.

aiSLCDiscreteOutputTable.name: aiSLCDiscreteOutputTable
aiSLCDiscreteOutputTable.description: Table of discrete input points indexed by point number. Includes description, configuration, and status information.

aislcdoutPointNumber.name: aislcdoutPointNumber
aislcdoutPointNumber.description: Output point number to which this table row applies.

aislcdoutDescription.name: aislcdoutDescription
aislcdoutDescription.description: Textual description of the point. Maximum length is 80 characters.

aislcdoutOutputEnable.name: aislcdoutOutputEnable
aislcdoutOutputEnable.description: Enable or disable this point. When the point is disabled, the output is immediately de-energized and remains so regardless of the values of other objects in this row. When the point is enabled, output is immediately set to its non-alarm state and operates according to the values of the other objects in this row.

aislcdoutMomentaryTimeout.name: aislcdoutMomentaryTimeout
aislcdoutMomentaryTimeout.description: If zero, the output will stay in the alarm state until it is returned to the normal state by some other event. If nonzero, this defines the time interval for momentary operation described in aislcdoutOutput. Maximum is 99.9 seconds.

aislcdouttl1AccessID.name: aislcdouttl1AccessID
aislcdouttl1AccessID.description: Unique TL1 access identifier for this point. Maximum length is 22 characters.

aislcdoutTrapEnable.name: aislcdoutTrapEnable
aislcdoutTrapEnable.description: Enable or disable traps. If enabled, a trap is sent whenever the point changes state.

aislcdoutAlarmStateOutput.name: aislcdoutAlarmStateOutput
aislcdoutAlarmStateOutput.description: Output that corresponds to the point's alarm state.

aislcdoutAlarmSeverity.name: aislcdoutAlarmSeverity
aislcdoutAlarmSeverity.description: Severity of the point's alarm state, or notReported(5) if the point does not generate an alarm.

aislcdoutNonAlarmStateText.name: aislcdoutNonAlarmStateText
aislcdoutNonAlarmStateText.description: Textual description of the point's non-alarm state. Maximum length is 80 characters.

aislcdoutAlarmStateText.name: aislcdoutAlarmStateText
aislcdoutAlarmStateText.description: Textual description of the point's alarm state. Maximum length is 80 characters.

aislcdoutOutput.name: aislcdoutOutput
aislcdoutOutput.description: On a read operation, this is the current output of the point. On a write operation when the output is controlled by aislcdoutEnergizeExpression, the write is rejected. Otherwise on a write operation, when set to de-energized, the output immediately assumes this state. When set to energized, the state of the output goes to the energized state, unless the output is already waiting for its aislcdoutMomentaryTimeout interval to elapse.

aislcdoutLastChangeTime.name: aislcdoutLastChangeTime
aislcdoutLastChangeTime.description: Textual representation of the time of the most recent output change. 24-hour format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS.

aislcdoutCurrentState.name: aislcdoutCurrentState
aislcdoutCurrentState.description: The point's current alarm state, or normal(5).

aislcdoutCurrentStateText.name: aislcdoutCurrentStateText
aislcdoutCurrentStateText.description: Textual description of the point's current state. This is either aislcdoutNonAlarmStateText or aislcdoutAlarmStateText.

aislcdoutEnergizeExpression.name: aislcdoutEnergizeExpression
aislcdoutEnergizeExpression.description: String that describes when this output goes into the energized state, as a function of a discrete input (or analog input for AIscout2). For AIscout, an integer >= 1 represents a discrete input, and '~' complements the input state. For AIscout2, this expression is a combination of analog and discrete inputs. Analog inputs are preceded by an 'A' and discrete inputs by a 'D'. The complement '~' works on a group of inputs. Also, multiple inputs may be specified as a comma separated list (1,3,5) or a hyphenated range (1-5). The expression is a combination of up to three ORs and as many ANDs as desired (i.e. a sum of 3 products). An empty string indicates manual control of the output point. AIscout examples: '15' -- energize the output when input 15 is alarmed (and deenergize when the input is normal). '~8' -- energize the output when input 8 is normal (and deenergize when the input is alarmed). AIscout2 examples: 'AH1,3,5' -- energize if the high alarm is active on analog inputs 1, 3 and 5. '~AH1-2&AL3' -- energize if analog inputs 1 and 2 are normal (not in the alarm state) AND analog input 3 is in the low alarm state. 'AH*|AL*|D*' -- energize if ANY analog is alarmed OR any discrete input is alarmed.

aislcdiscPowerSupplyStatus.name: aislcdiscPowerSupplyStatus
aislcdiscPowerSupplyStatus.description: Status of the power supply. okay(1) or trouble(2). When the SLC is booted, this indicates okay(1) until the software determines the correct status.

aislcdiscFiber1TransmitterStatus.name: aislcdiscFiber1TransmitterStatus
aislcdiscFiber1TransmitterStatus.description: Status of the first fiber port's transmitter.

aislcdiscFiber2TransmitterStatus.name: aislcdiscFiber2TransmitterStatus
aislcdiscFiber2TransmitterStatus.description: Status of the second fiber port's transmitter.

aislcdiscAnalogInputPowerSupplyStatus.name: aislcdiscAnalogInputPowerSupplyStatus
aislcdiscAnalogInputPowerSupplyStatus.description: Status of the analog input power supply fuse.
